name: Kiwi T-shirt
description:
From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range.

Flightless, nocturnal and iconic, the kiwi is New Zealand's most famous bird. There are five  species - the North Island brown being the most common. A strong sense of smell, whiskers, and fur-like feathers make the kiwi the badger of birds!

Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric.

name: Kids Tuatara T-shirt
description: From our kids' New Zealand t-shirt design range. Found only in New Zealand, the Tuatara has been around for over 200 million years! Each of our kids t-shirts is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric.

name: Kea Baby Onesie
description:
From our baby onesie New Zealand design range.
 
Found only in New Zealand, the Kea is the world's only alpine parrot.

Each of our baby onesies is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!) on 100% cotton.

name: Archival Tumbleweed Prints
description: Our full range of New Zealand line drawings are available as archival prints. Get a piece of Tumbleweed art for your wall. Designs are printed on archival watercolour paper - they have the feel and the weight of the original. View the full range below: Tumbleweed Prints Please choose your design and size - we print to A4 or A3.

name: Kaka Sweatshirt
description: From our range of New Zealand sweatshirt designs. This lowland cousin of the alpine kea is found in pockets of forest throughout NZ. They are often seen and heard in mischievous gangs using their strong beaks for ripping up bark to find food. Our sweatshirts are thick and warm - 350 GSM, 80% Cotton, 20% Poly, Anti-pill fabric, Raglan Sleeves and are hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!) To learn more about KakaWatchNZ click here

name: Tongariro Crossing Merino Long Sleeve Tee
description:
From our merino range of New Zealand designs. 

This is a geological cross section of one of the worlds best 1 day treks along a line of stunning crater lakes.

Our 100% merino long sleeves t-shirts are hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!) Sizes can be worn unisex - womens style is slightly more fitted, with a lower neck.

name: Mohua/Yellowhead T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. WINNER - Bird of the Year 2013 - The Mohua/Yellowhead is a protected threatened endemic species once commonly found in forests throughout the South Island of New Zealand. Introduced rats and stoats lead to large declines in mohua numbers and confined them to fragmented patches of beech forest but mohua are prolific breeders, and when predator numbers are controlled they can thrive. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about Mohua/yellowhead conservation click here

name: John Dory T-shirt
description:
From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range.

When approaching prey front on, the thin-bodied John Dory is hardly visible to them however when faced with predators he can appear much larger than he is by turning side on, flashing his big ‘evil eye’ spot and raising his large dorsal spines. 

Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric.

name: Gecko T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. One of the two genera of geckos endemic to New Zealand, Naultinus or green gecko have thousands of hair-like structures (setae) on their toe pads that allow them to stick to almost any surface, making them excellent tree climbers. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about the Rimutaka Forest Park Charitable Trust's Gecko Conservation work Click here

name: NZ Snail T-shirt
description: This genus of carnivorous land snails  - the Powelliphanta - are unique to New Zealand. Found throughout the country, they are most commonly encountered in the North West of the South Island.

name: Morepork/Ruru T-shirt
description:
From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. More often heard than seen, the ruru is New Zealand’s only surviving native owl. Their super sensitive hearing and night vision, combined with near silent flight and 270 degree rotating head make them highly proficient nocturnal predators, feasting mostly on large invertebrates. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about the Morepork Conservation at the Wingspan Centre Click here

SPECIAL OFFER!! When you wear your Tumbleweed Morepork/Ruru tee (adult or kids) to the Wingspan Centre in Rotorua you get...

name: Takahē T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. This stocky cousin of the pukeko was once thought to be extinct. Since it's rediscovery in 1948, the takahē has been the focus of a hands on conservation effort to increase the population and save this beautiful, dinosaur of a bird. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about the Mitre 10 Takahē Rescue click here

name: Kaka T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. This lowland cousin of the alpine kea is found in pockets of forest throughout NZ. They are often seen and heard in mischievous gangs using their strong beaks for ripping up bark to find food. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about KakaWatchNZ click here

name: Archey's Frog T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. This primitive frog is critically endangered (IUCN), and now only found in small pockets of the North Island, making it one of the rarest frogs in the world. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about the DOC's Archey's Frog Conservation click here

name: Karearea/NZ Falcon T-shirt
description:
From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. WINNER - Bird of the Year 2012 Small, fast and feisty, Karearea can reach speeds of 230km/h and will aggressively defend their territory. Half the size of the Australasian swamp harrier, they are our only surviving, endemic bird of prey. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about Karearea/NZ Falcon Conservation at the Wingspan Centre Click here

SPECIAL OFFER!! When you wear your Tumbleweed Karearea/NZ Falcon tee (adult or kids) to the Wingspan Centre in Rotorua you get...

name: Little Blue Penguin T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. The little blue penguin is the smallest penguin in the world! Their tiny, but highly adapted wings take them on epic fishing trips - covering 75kms in a typical 15 hour journey! Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about the Places for Penguins project click here

name: Kea T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. The world's only alpine parrot is notoriously mischievous by nature. They are known to damage cars, tents, and jandals with their strong beaks. Luckily their cheeky, charming personalities ensure there are no hard feelings. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about the Kea Conservation Trust click here

name: Tuatara T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. New Zealand's two species of tuatara are the last surviving members of an ancient lineage of reptiles that lived over 200 million years ago - when dinosaurs roamed the earth! Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about Tuatara conservation on Matiu/Somes Island click here

name: Kakapo T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. Being the world's only flightless parrot, and the heaviest too, the Kakapo is truly unique. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. To learn more about the Kakapo Recovery programme Click here

name: Shag T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. Often seen drying their wings, the shag is a free-dive-fishing master! Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric.

name: South Island Cross Section T-shirt
description: From our adults' New Zealand t-shirt design range. This is a geological cross section of the actively faulted, spectacular countryside of New Zealand's South Island. Each tee is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric.

name: Tumbleweed Merino Scarves
description:
These 2 metre long scarves can be worn in so many ways - a scarf, a wrap, a top, a headscarf, a travel blanket for tropical forests... the list goes on! Being soft, fine, 100% NZ merino, you can use this scarf in the heat or in the cold. Each scarf is hand-pulled using water based inks (heat cured to last!) Scarves are available in the following designs: pohutukawa, mountain flax, and tumbleweed. Please email us if you would like any of our other designs and we can do a custom order. Each purchase comes with a "how to" guide on wearing your new scarf. Colours of merino vary. We will update this page with new colours as they become available. Dimensions: 2 metres long, 41 cm wide.

Our 100% merino long sleeve t-shirts are hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!) Sizes can be worn unisex - womens style is slightly more fitted, with a lower neck. name: Kiwi Baby Onesie
description:
From our baby onesie New Zealand design range.

Flightless, nocturnal and iconic, the kiwi is New Zealand's most famous bird. There are five  species - the North Island brown being the most common. A strong sense of smell, whiskers, and fur-like feathers make the kiwi the badger of birds!

Each baby onesie is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!) on 100% cotton.

name: Archey's Frog Baby Onesie
description:
From our baby onesie New Zealand design range.

This primitive frog is critically endangered (IUCN), and now only found in small pockets of the North Island, making it one of the rarest frogs in the world.

Each baby onesie is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!) on 100% cotton.

name: Kids Karearea/NZ Falcon T-shirt
description:
From our kids' New Zealand t-shirt design range.

Small, fast and feisty, Karearea can reach speeds of 230km/h and will aggressively defend their territory. Half the size of the Australasian swamp harrier, they are our only surviving, endemic bird of prey. 

Each of our kids t-shirts is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric.

name: Kids Morepork/Ruru T-shirt
description: From our kids' New Zealand t-shirt design range. More often heard than seen, the ruru is New Zealand’s only surviving native owl. Their super sensitive hearing and night vision, combined with near silent flight and 270 degree rotating head make them highly proficient nocturnal predators, feasting mostly on large invertebrates. Each of our kids t-shirts is hand-printed using water based inks (heat cured to last!). 180 GSM 100% cotton, pre-shrunk fabric. SPECIAL OFFER!!
